{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783924579002,"sessionID":"ses_0a6050605ffekKPL0ZIbz84Q5J","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_Gby06AlOIwbF3ByVMUFOc5Oo","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/review/xhigh-confirm/lineages/confirm-a/deep-review-strategy.md","offset":1,"limit":1000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/review/xhigh-confirm/lineages/confirm-a/deep-review-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Review Strategy: sk-code Split-Doc Template Alignment\n2: \n3: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n4: \n5: ### Purpose\n6: \n7: Track a four-pass review of the completed split-document template alignment packet and its declared sk-code deliverables.\n8: \n9: ### Usage\n10: \n11: Each LEAF iteration reviews one dimension, updates the machine-owned state, and rotates to the next uncovered dimension. Convergence is telemetry-only until iteration 4.\n12: \n13: ## 2. TOPIC\n14: \n15: Review `.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment` against its structural conformance, preservation, link-repair, and evidence claims.\n16: \n17: ## 3. REVIEW DIMENSIONS (remaining)\n18: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n19: - [x] D1 Correctness: behavior and structural claims match the current files — score 4/5 (iteration 1, PASS; historical preservation replay deferred)\n20: - [x] D2 Security: documentation examples and trust-boundary claims do not create in-scope hazards — score 4/5 (iteration 2, PASS with one P2 framing advisory)\n21: - [x] D3 Traceability: requirements, checked evidence, and implementation surfaces agree — score 4/5 (iteration 3, PASS with two P2 evidence/handoff advisories)\n22: - [x] D4 Maintainability: resulting resource documents remain clear and mechanically supportable — score 4/5 (iteration 4, PASS; three existing P2 advisories carried unchanged)\n23: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n24: \n25: ## 4. NON-GOALS\n26: \n27: - Do not modify the reviewed spec or sk-code resource documents.\n28: - Do not reopen unrelated content-quality concerns unless they contradict this packet's completion claims.\n29: - Do not review paths outside the spec packet and the three declared sk-code surface resource/asset trees.\n30: \n31: ## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n32: \n33: - Dispatch exactly four iterations under `stopPolicy=max-iterations` unless an unrecoverable workflow error occurs.\n34: - Treat convergence before iteration 4 as telemetry and broaden the next angle.\n35: - Never stop with missing iteration narrative, canonical JSONL record, or delta file.\n36: \n37: ## 6. COMPLETED DIMENSIONS\n38: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n39: \n40: | Dimension | Verdict | Iteration | Summary |\n41: |-----------|---------|-----------|---------|\n42: | Correctness | PASS (4/5) | 1 | 163-file current-state structure, naming, overview order, duplicate, and link checks passed; historical preservation was not replayed. |\n43: | Security | PASS (4/5) | 2 | Documentation-only scope confirmed; one packet-added usage wrapper frames a pre-existing unconstrained script loader too broadly (P2). |\n44: | Traceability | PASS (4/5) | 3 | R1-R3/R5 and current corpus evidence align; stale follow-up prose and non-replayable checklist/task evidence contracts produced two P2 advisories. |\n45: | Maintainability | PASS (4/5) | 4 | Template/validator/link-scan ownership is documented; stabilization found no new P0/P1 and carried the three distinct P2 advisories unchanged. |\n46: \n47: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n48: \n49: ## 7. RUNNING FINDINGS\n50: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n51: - **P0 (Critical):** 0 active\n52: - **P1 (Major):** 0 active\n53: - **P2 (Minor):** 3 active\n54: - **Delta this iteration:** +0 P0, +0 P1, +0 P2\n55: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n56: \n57: ## 8. WHAT WORKED\n58: \n59: - Iteration 1: A scope-wide deterministic sweep reproduced the 163-file 65/95/3 distribution and narrowed two literal-heading candidates plus one documented link exception for direct adjudication.\n60: - Iteration 1: Focused reads ruled out all three candidates without severity inflation; direct packet evidence remained sufficient after Spec Memory was unavailable.\n61: - Iteration 2: Exact sink searches narrowed security-sensitive examples to dynamic scripts, cookies, DOM sinks, shell input, and secrets; focused reads separated clearly labeled anti-patterns from one in-scope framing advisory.\n62: - Iteration 2: Counterevidence in the remediated third-party loader supplied the concrete allowlist/SRI model needed to scope P2-001 without escalating it.\n63: - Iteration 3: Explicit-root corpus inventories reconciled the current 65/95/3 distribution without repeating the prior broad-root scope error.\n64: - Iteration 3: Packet-to-resource reads separated current implementation truth from stale follow-up prose and preserved historical provenance as an explicit limitation.\n65: - Iteration 4: Packet-level template, validator, surface-scan, and whole-hub link guidance supplied durable maintenance ownership without requiring a new advisory.\n66: - Iteration 4: Direct rereads kept P2-001, P2-002, and P2-003 distinct and unchanged while the stabilization search found no overlooked P0/P1 class.\n67: \n68: ## 9. WHAT FAILED\n69: \n70: - Spec Memory context lookup timed out twice; packet docs and direct file evidence are the fallback.\n71: - Iteration 1: The rendered prompt names review-depth v2 envelopes but omits their field-level schema; the canonical record retains explicit applicability, selection, coverage, ledger, and limitations.\n72: - Iteration 2: Historical provenance for risky body snippets was not replayed against a pre-change baseline; the iteration relies on the packet's R4 preservation claim and limits the active finding to current wrapper framing.\n73: - Iteration 3: Historical R4 preservation, commit sequencing, and push evidence remain non-replayable because task/checklist rows do not carry the commands or output pointers their protocols claim.\n74: - Iteration 4: The declared `code-quality/references` root is absent; one scoped Grep request returned parent-directory hits, which were discarded and cannot support review conclusions.\n75: \n76: ## 10. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n77: \n78: - Repeated Spec Memory calls are blocked for this lineage after two timeouts; use direct reads and exact searches.\n79: - The absent `code-quality/references` root must not be searched again; treat it as empty and use only the existing `code-quality/assets` root at synthesis.\n80: \n81: ## 10A. SATURATED / SWEPT DIMENSIONS AND EXPANSION FRONTIER\n82: - Completed pivots: 0\n83: - Failed pivots: 0\n84: - Audited overrides: 0\n85: - Swept: none yet\n86: - Pivot lineage: none yet\n87: - Remaining frontier: none recorded\n88: \n89: ## 11. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n90: \n91: - Resource-map coverage: target packet has no `resource-map.md`; the workflow coverage gate is skipped.\n92: - Iteration 1: Two apparent missing `When to Use` headings were semantic-heading variants with concrete usage content; ruled out by direct reads.\n93: - Iteration 1: The illustrative `/specs/005-example.com/...` link is the documented pre-existing non-navigational artifact, not a renamed-file referrer.\n94: - Iteration 1 limitation: historical verbatim-content preservation was not replayed against a pre-change baseline and remains explicit traceability follow-up.\n95: - Iteration 2: The disclosed cookie contradiction is no longer current because the file now distinguishes non-sensitive client-set cookies from server-set `HttpOnly` session cookies.\n96: - Iteration 2: The disclosed arbitrary-input third-party loader concern is no longer current because the file now validates HTTPS, allowlists hosts, and notes SRI.\n97: - Iteration 2: P0/P1 escalation for the remaining `resource_loading.md` loader was ruled out because its shown caller uses a static URL and the reviewed target is documentation-only.\n98: - Iteration 3: Current cookie and allowlist defects named by the summary follow-up were ruled out by live file reads; the defect is stale packet prose, not current resource behavior.\n99: - Iteration 3: P2-001 refinement/duplication was ruled out because the traceability findings concern packet evidence and handoff wording rather than the existing loader-framing instance.\n100: - Iteration 4: A new generic ownership finding was ruled out because the packet names the template/package authority, per-file validator, snake-case scan, and whole-hub link scan.\n101: - Iteration 4: P2-001/P2-002/P2-003 merge, refinement, severity change, and resolution were ruled out; their producers and remediation surfaces remain distinct.\n102: \n103: ## 12. NEXT FOCUS\n104: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n105: - Dimension: synthesis/adversarial replay\n106: - Focus area: terminal synthesis of cumulative findings and adversarial replay of carried gate-relevant claims\n107: - Reason: all four dimensions are complete at the max-iteration boundary with three active P2 advisories and no P0/P1\n108: - Rotation status: 4 of 4 dimensions complete; no fifth review iteration\n109: - Blocked/productive carry-forward: historical baseline replay and the absent `code-quality/references` root remain exhausted; direct cited evidence and cumulative state remain productive\n110: - Required evidence: reconcile P2-001/P2-002/P2-003 against the registry, replay release gates, preserve R4 search debt, and verify state/delta identity before final report rendering\n111: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n112: \n113: ## 13. KNOWN CONTEXT\n114: \n115: ### Bounded Context Snapshot\n116: \n117: - Target pointers: `spec.md`, `plan.md`, `tasks.md`, `checklist.md`, `implementation-summary.md`, and all Markdown under the declared `code-opencode`, `code-webflow`, and `code-quality` reference/asset trees.